By Esther Egbe

Super Eagles goalkeeper Ikechukwu Ezenwa has disclosed that the need for regular game time and enhancement of his career are reasons why he is leaving Enyimba FC of Aba,National Daily learnt.

The former FC IfeanyiUbah Number 1 spoke with National Daily during a chat
on his decision to quit the People’s Elephant.

Ezenwa explained that “I needed to play regularly. Its a very important decision in my career. Although I had a good time at Enyimba but as a player you have your decisions to make and I’ve taken the decision to play for Katsina United,”.

Interestingly Ezenwa did stress that the agreement with Katsina United is a verbal agreement with nothing official finalised.
